rs.Examining Hindi classics, translations from English poetry, literary criticism, and little-known popular works, Ritter combines translations with fresh literary analysis to show the pivotal role of nature in how modernity was understood. Bringing a new body of literature to English-language readers, Kama's Flowers also reveals the origins of an influential visual culture that resonates today in Bollywood cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHindi poetryy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHindi poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aNature in literature. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Hindu Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Indic.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438435671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438435671/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles